  "original_title": "\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b86\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1?: \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0b9f\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Retrenchment soon?: Minister takes action",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Power Minister Kanchana Wijesekara has emphasized the need to restructure state-owned enterprises.",
        "In a recent tweet, he pointed out that political decisions, political appointments, mismanagement and inefficiency led to the downfall of state-owned enterprises.",
        "The minister mentioned that he did not think that the majority of civil servants would survive or be employed in the private sector and that performance-based salaries were essential.",
        "Although Sri Lanka Electricity Board, Sri Lanka Petroleum Corporation and Petroleum Storage Terminal have skilled employees, the majority are unskilled, he said.",
        "He also pointed out that 500 people instead of 4200 people in Sri Lanka Petroleum Corporation, Petroleum Storage Terminal and half of the 26,000 employees in the Electricity Board can work efficiently."
      ],
